This paper involves the intersection of Topological Data Analysis and Machine Learning, which is a popular area of research in computer science. The use of persistence diagrams and featurization methods suggests that the paper may fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the adaptive partitioning method and parameter selection framework involve algorithms and data structures, which could place the paper in the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The application of the method to example data sets suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). The use of continuous functions and optimization methods may also suggest the category of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper involves the development of new methods for utilizing persistence diagrams, which could place it in the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
